Comments.Message:
I am not the Dev but i have played withthe three model a bit, so this answer might not be perfect, but i think it is atleast 'on the right track';
at some point in gear, you will have 'enough' spirit to not go OOM in a fight.  at this point, Spirit will not have 'much' advantage, and the model will likely reforge/gem toward a differnt stat.

if you ARE still going OOM, then you can adjust the boss handler as needed to make the fight longer, so that the model is forced to build up a larger spirit pool for you.
